cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.PF 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the analysis of Internet traffic over a long period of time. The paper also uses multiscale analysis and random projections to study the scaling behavior of the traffic, which are techniques commonly used in the field of networking and internet architecture. 

The paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the analysis of network traffic and the mechanisms producing them. 

Additionally, the paper could be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory) as it deals with the statistical analysis of data and the characterization of scaling behavior. 

The sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possibility as the study of Internet traffic can have implications for security and privacy. 

Finally, the sub-category of cs.PF (Performance) could also be relevant as the study of Internet traffic can provide insights into the performance of networks and systems.
